        "title": "feat(website): add macOS-themed marketing landing page",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds a marketing landing page for Vox under `website/` — a self-hosted bridge between Twilio Media Streams and OpenAI Realtime. This is a standalone Vite + React + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS site with its own `package.json`, intentionally not wired into the bridge server's build/test/typecheck pipeline.\n\n## What's included\n\n- **Scaffold**: Vite + React 19 + TypeScript, Tailwind CSS 4 (CSS-based config), Framer Motion, Lenis smooth scrolling, Lucide icons, dark macOS-inspired design system.\n- **Sections**: Hero, Features, Architecture, Highlights, UseCases, Quickstart, Terminal, CTABanner, Footer.\n- **Components**: Navbar, Dock, MacWindow, Preloader, SpotlightCard, TiltCard, MagneticButton, HeroIllustration, Parallax, plus shared icons/hooks/easing utilities.\n- **Brand assets & OG images**: app icon, wordmark, favicon, hero illustration, social preview images (`public/`), with a `generate-og-png.mjs` script.\n- **Deployment config**: `vercel.json`, `netlify.toml`, `_headers`, `robots.txt`.\n- **PR proof**: landing page screenshot under `website/screenshots/`.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [ ] `cd website && pnpm install && pnpm dev` — verify the page renders and animations/scroll behave correctly\n- [ ] `pnpm run build` — verify static output builds cleanly to `website/dist/`\n- [ ] `pnpm run typecheck` — no type errors\n- [ ] Root `pnpm run lint` still passes (website files are covered by the root formatter)\n",
